title: National day of mourning for Bondi victims | 9 News Australia
description: A National Day of Mourning will be held in January to remember the victims of the Bondi terror attack.  The Prime Minister also announced a minute of silence, to be held across the nation on Sunday evening, with Australians invited to light a candle at 6:47pm as a symbol of remembrance. #9News

title: Government introducing national gun buyback scheme | 9 News Australia
description: #BREAKING: The government will introduce a national gun buyback scheme in the wake of the Bondi shooting, to purchase and destroy surplus, newly banned and illegal weapons.  The Prime Minister says there are more than four million firearms currently in Australia, more than at the time of the Port Arthur massacre 30 years ago. #9News
